function count_model_rows(df::DataFrame) -> DataFrame;
    groupby = df.groupby("model"));
    result = groupby.size();
    return result;
end
```

This function takes a `DataFrame` as input and groups the data by model using the `groupby` method. Then, it calculates the number of rows for each group using the `size` method. Finally, it returns the result DataFrame.
